snippet: A federal judge granted a temporary restraining order blocking enforcement of a new Wisconsin law that bans doctors who lack admitting privileges at nearby hospitals from performing abortions.
abstract: Federal Judge William Conley grants temporary restraining order blocking enforcement of new Wisconsin law that bans doctors who lack admitting privileges at nearby hospitals from performing abortions.
lead_paragraph: A federal judge granted a temporary restraining order blocking enforcement of a new Wisconsin law that bans doctors who lack admitting privileges at nearby hospitals from performing abortions.

headline.main: Wisconsin: Enforcement of Abortion Law Is Delayed
